Inline profile pictures in the chat (Kitty graphics protocol).

Adds an opt-in feature: each message header line gets the author's
avatar rendered next to it via Kitty's image protocol. Off by default
(set `inline_pfp = True` in config.ini to enable). No-op on
non-Kitty terminals.

Mechanics:
- New module endcord/pfp.py owns the avatar cache + Kitty escape
  sequence wrangling.
- message.py and app.py stop discarding the "avatar" hash so the
  renderer can find it per message.
- When enabled, the chat formatter's format_message / format_newline /
  format_reply / format_reactions / format_interaction are prefixed
  with 3 spaces so the 2-cell avatar doesn't cover text.
- tui.draw_chat calls into place_inline_pfps after curses redraws,
  which deletes the previous Kitty placements and re-issues them for
  the currently-visible header rows. App-side _build_pfp_lines maps
  chat_map entries to (user_id, avatar_id) tuples.

Risks: Kitty placements layer on top of curses cells, so anything
that scrolls / partially redraws the chat without going through
draw_chat will leave orphaned images on screen. The feature is
gated to make rollback trivial.

